.TH VACUUM-MAIL-APP 1 "May 2026" "vacuum-mail-app 0.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vacuum-mail-app \- vacuum the Mail.app Envelope Index SQLite database
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vacuum-mail-app
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vacuum-mail-app
quits Mail.app if it is running, runs
.B sqlite3 vacuum
against the Envelope Index database stored under
.IR ~/Library/Mail/<version>/MailData/ ,
prints the byte counts before and after along with the percentage change, and then reopens Mail.
.SH OPTIONS
This utility does not accept any command-line options.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
The database was vacuumed successfully.
.TP
1
An error occurred (for example, sw_vers or sqlite3 failed, or the Envelope Index file was not
found).
